# header
#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:27
msgid "## A Brief History"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:30
msgid ""
"[Software Carpentry]({{ site.swc_site }}) was founded in 1998 with the mission of teaching lab skills for research computing.\n"
"[Data Carpentry]({{ site.dc_site }}) was founded in 2014 with the mission of building communities teaching universal data literacy."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:33
msgid ""
"Also in 2014, [Library Carpentry]({{ site.lc_site }}) was founded with the "
"mission of teaching data skills to people working in library- and "
"information-related roles."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:35
msgid ""
"On January 1, 2018, Software Carpentry and Data Carpentry merged\n"
"their projects to form a new project called\n"
"[The Carpentries]({{ site.carpentries_site }})\n"
"under the fiscal sponsorship of\n"
"[Community Initiatives](https://communityin.org/).\n"
"Within this new organization structure, Software Carpentry and Data Carpentry retain their individual identities as Lesson Programs of the Carpentries.\n"
"On November 1, 2018, The Carpentries Executive Council\n"
"approved [Library Carpentry]({{ site.lc_site }})\n"
"as the third official Lesson Program of the Carpentries."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:45
msgid ""
"The Carpentries project comprises communities of Instructors, Trainers,\n"
"Maintainers, helpers, and supporters from\n"
"[Software Carpentry]({{ site.swc_site }}), [Data Carpentry]({{ site.dc_site }}) and [Library Carpentry]({{ site.lc_site }})\n"
"who share a mission to teach foundational computational and data science skills."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:50
msgid "![A brief history](../fig/SWCDChistory.png)"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:52
msgid ""
"You can learn more about the history and goals of each Lesson Program by reading\n"
"\"[Software Carpentry: Lessons Learned](https://f1000research.com/articles/3-62/v2)\",\n"
"\"[Data Carpentry: Workshops to Increase Data Literacy for Researchers](http://ijdc.net/index.php/ijdc/article/view/10.1.135)\" and\n"
"\"[Library Carpentry: software skills training for library professionals](https://www.liberquarterly.eu/article/10.18352/lq.10176/)\"\"."
msgstr ""

