# header
#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:111
msgid "### Materials"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:113
msgid ""
"Note that the individual Software Carpentry, Data Carpentry, and Library Carpentry lessons\n"
"materials are freely available under a permissive [open license]({{ page.root }}{% link LICENSE.md %}).\n"
"This means that you may use them in contexts outside a Carpentries workshop (e.g. as material\n"
"introduced into a longer course, as a standalone 2-3 hour session, as homework exercises, etc.)\n"
"provided you cite the original source."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:119
msgid ""
"It is only when you want to run a branded \"Carpentries\" workshop using the materials\n"
"that the requirements listed above are needed."
msgstr ""

# header
#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:122
msgid "### What is the Core Curriculum?"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:124
msgid ""
"A Software Carpentry workshop must include [lessons](https://software-carpentry.org/lessons/index.html)\n"
"on version control (e.g. Git), the UNIX shell,\n"
"and a programming language (e.g. R or Python)."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:128
msgid ""
"A Data Carpentry workshop must include a Data Carpentry [lesson](https://datacarpentry.org/lessons/)\n"
"on data organization and three\n"
"other modules in the same domain from the Data Carpentry curriculum.\n"
"Published curricula include the Ecology, Genomics, Social Science and Geospatial workshop materials.\n"
"Additionally, Astronomy, Digital humanities, Economics and Image analysis curriculum are under development."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:134
msgid ""
"A Library Carpentry workshop must include three to four of the\n"
"[core lessons](https://librarycarpentry.org/lessons/#core-curriculum), which include an introduction to data, the UNIX shell, OpenRefine, and Git.\n"
"Library Carpentry also maintains an \"extended\" set of lessons\n"
"that can be taught in addition to the core curriculum\n"
"These lessons are taught infrequently or are under development and include:\n"
"SQL, webscraping, Python and an introduction to data for archivists."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:141
msgid ""
"Within these guidelines, there is flexibility in which episodes of the lesson you cover,\n"
"which exercises you use, and whether you include optional materials (e.g. callouts) and\n"
"optional episodes."
msgstr ""

# header
#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:145
msgid "### Who Can Teach What"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:147
msgid ""
"People who have gone through the two-day instructor training course and completed\n"
"the [the checkout process]({{ page.root }}/checkout/) are considered \"certified\"\n"
"Carpentries instructors and can teach curricula for **any** of the lesson programs\n"
"(Software Carpentry, Data Carpentry, or Library Carpentry)\n"
"as they feel able. While instructor badges\n"
"may list a primary lesson program affiliation, instructors are **not** required to certify separately for each. For more\n"
"information, see the description of [the instructor checkout procedure]({{ page.root }}/checkout/)."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:155
msgid ""
"Note that as long as you have at least one certified instructor, the other\n"
"instructors and helpers at a branded workshop do not have to be certified. We\n"
"rely on the judgment of local organizers to recruit and orient volunteers who\n"
"will embody the Carpentries ethos and practices."
msgstr ""

# blockquote, which can be cascaded
#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:160
msgid "> ## Local Support"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/21-carpentries.md:161
msgid ""
">\n"
"> There is a great list\n"
">\n"
"> here in the handbook [Helper Checklist and Suggestions](https://docs.carpentries.org/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.html#helper-checklist)."
